{
  "text": "Suggestive correlations were found between genome size and proxies of environmental temperature (MAL, MAL+MDE, & MDE) for the crustaceans in this study (Table 2 ) both with (PGLS) and without phylogenetic contrast (OLS/lm). Contrary to the findings in amphipods species from Lake Baikal in [CITATION_1] , a phylogenetic structuring was observed for genome size variation in this study (\u03bb \u2248 1), likely due to the use of a generalized phylogeny based on taxonomy (equal branch lengths) rather than transcriptome data (unequal branch lengths).",
